metadata.name: Solace #216
metadata.description:
Solace is an algorithm that generates artworks of sand dunes. It draws hundreds of thousands of tiny points according to a probability distribution calculated from the positions of the dunes.

The logic to divide the dunes into light and dark sides is simple, but produces some interesting chaotic behaviour. These are details that weren't hard-coded but emerge organically, such as the patterns on the spines of the dunes or the stripes around their bases.

Please note that the algorithm can take some time to run, especially when the number of dunes is high.

Created by lunarean.

metadata.name: Complicare #101
metadata.description:
Complicare is my first "still" generative work, and an exercise in minimalism.

Inspired by pioneers like Sol Lewitt and Frank Stella, as well as current fx_hash artists such as Rev Dan Catt and Yazid, this work attempts to balance a diverse visual output with a restricted generative system. I also wanted to focus on honing my abilities to add texture to the digital canvas, taking cues from other great artists on here like William Mapan and Hevey.

Each piece has one of 17 different layouts and one of 6 different color palettes.

Thanks to all of the artists on fx_hash for inspiring me every day to make more art, and particularly to dcarcher for some really insightful artistic perspective and feedback.

metadata.name: Hexaëder #141
metadata.description:
Hexaëder (cube) is a research into abstraction and a search for a balance between simplification and visual complexity.

No matter how simple and unambiguous things appear to be, in reality they are often more complex. Enjoy the simple, explore the complex.

Hexaeder has a wide variety of possible outcomes. I have put together 10 different color palettes; the number of cubes ranges from 10 to 401 (18 different grids); each cell can have 4 different background patterns; each cube can be filled in 4 distinct ways; there are 5 line colors and 16 different "cube figures"; the vignette can be black or be the color of the palette, and there are several "texture settings". This results in over 1.8 million possibilities.

For more information see: https://www.behance.net/gallery/131114761/Hexaeder-Flattened-cubes

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #268
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x  16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting
b: Toggles b-side
